The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, has confirmed 34 new cases of Covid-19 in Nigeria.
In a tweet on its official Twitter page on Wednesday, the centre disclosed that the confirmed cases were in Lagos, Kano, Katsina, Niger, and Delta States.
The confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria now totals 407.
NCDC wrote: “ Thirty-four new cases of #COVID19 have been reported as follows:
18 Lagos
12 in Kano
2 in Katsina
1 in Delta
1 in Niger
“As at 11:20 pm 15th April there are 407 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. 128 have been discharged with 12 deaths.”

			
